Spec: Container
Purpose:
  Build and expose application service and command instances through explicit constructor wiring.

Structure:
  container.ts: Application container implementation.
  container.test.ts: Container tests.

Owns:
  container.ts
  container.test.ts

References:
  commands/check-update.sdd
  commands/init.sdd
  commands/update.sdd
  infrastructure/fetch-client.sdd
  infrastructure/file-system.sdd
  infrastructure/temp-directory.sdd
  services/bootstrap-metadata/service.sdd
  services/config/service.sdd
  services/config/readers/environment-reader.sdd
  services/logger/service.sdd
  services/specdd-version/service.sdd
  services/distribution-client/service.sdd
  services/update-checker/service.sdd
  services/signature-verifier/service.sdd
  services/distribution-applier/service.sdd
  services/distribution-installer/service.sdd

Must:
  Construct shared service instances in one place.
  Construct infrastructure adapters in one place.
  Construct command instances in one place.
  Pass service dependencies through constructor parameters.
  Expose the config service.
  Expose the logger service.
  Expose the SpecDD version service.
  Expose the bootstrap metadata service.
  Expose the distribution client service.
  Expose the update checker service.
  Expose the signature verifier service.
  Expose the distribution applier service.
  Expose the distribution installer service.
  Expose the check-update command instance.
  Expose the init command instance.
  Expose the update command instance.
  Let commands receive the Container instance instead of constructing services directly.

Must not:
  Use autowiring, decorators, reflection, or a dependency injection framework.
  Instantiate shared services in command handlers.
  Hide dependencies behind global service instances.

Depends on:
  FetchClient
  FileSystem
  TempDirectory
  Config
  Logger
  SpecDDVersion
  BootstrapMetadata
  DistributionClient
  UpdateChecker
  SignatureVerifier
  DistributionApplier
  DistributionInstaller
  Check Update Command
  Init Command
  Update Command

Exposes:
  Container
  Container.specDDVersion
  Container.bootstrapMetadata
  Container.checkUpdateCommand
  Container.initCommand
  Container.updateCommand
